You said you found him
one day and took him in...

00:14:56.487 --> 00:14:59.487
But it seems like the Inspectors
know a lot more than that...

00:14:59.521 --> 00:15:02.021
So what kind
of child was he?

00:15:02.054 --> 00:15:03.721
He was an ordinary kid.

00:15:03.754 --> 00:15:05.321
You're wrong.

00:15:05.354 --> 00:15:07.554
He's always been
a strange one.

00:15:07.587 --> 00:15:08.987
I mean, when he knew
my heart wasn't beating,

00:15:09.021 --> 00:15:10.354
it didn't faze him.

00:15:10.387 --> 00:15:12.687
Almost like
he expected it.

00:15:12.721 --> 00:15:14.021
And even with Minai.

00:15:14.054 --> 00:15:16.354
He knew she was
a Shikabane Hime,

00:15:16.387 --> 00:15:19.787
but he treated her as if
she was an regular girl.

00:15:19.821 --> 00:15:21.021
I find it hard to believe

00:15:21.054 --> 00:15:22.787
that there's an
ordinary kid anywhere

00:15:22.821 --> 00:15:26.254
who could do all of that.

00:15:26.287 --> 00:15:28.387
If I remember correctly...

00:15:28.421 --> 00:15:30.987
he was about three
when he came here.

00:15:31.021 --> 00:15:34.287
Such a sad
and useless child.

00:15:34.321 --> 00:15:37.621
He didn't know how to put on
clothes, how to use tableware.

00:15:37.654 --> 00:15:39.587
The kid didn't even know
how to use the toilet.

00:15:39.621 --> 00:15:43.954
Nothing. Forget about any
emotional understanding.

00:15:43.987 --> 00:15:47.721
But one day,
something in him changed.

00:15:47.754 --> 00:15:50.287
He was different.

00:15:52.287 --> 00:15:54.387
What do you mean
you adopted him?

00:15:54.421 --> 00:15:56.387
Well, he was on the
riverside, crying.

00:15:56.421 --> 00:15:57.521
I had to do something.

00:15:57.554 --> 00:16:00.521
And bringing him
home was the answer?

