Don't listen to him.
I think it's great...

00:16:02.954 --> 00:16:05.687
He's your
friend now, right?

00:16:05.721 --> 00:16:06.987
Ouri had never
shown any interest

00:16:07.021 --> 00:16:09.321
towards other
kids up until then.

00:16:09.354 --> 00:16:11.321
Or anything for
that matter.

00:16:11.354 --> 00:16:12.687
And the very
first thing in this world

00:16:12.721 --> 00:16:15.754
that caught his attention
was a small, helpless life.

00:16:15.787 --> 00:16:17.521
You couldn't say he
was a good caretaker.

00:16:17.554 --> 00:16:19.954
He was much too clumsy
and short-sighted.

00:16:19.987 --> 00:16:23.554
But it seemed the kid was coming
back to life little by little.

00:16:27.487 --> 00:16:28.821
The poor thing.

00:16:28.854 --> 00:16:31.421
We'll hold a memorial
service for him.

00:16:31.454 --> 00:16:32.921
Riko, would you mind
grabbing a set of work gloves

00:16:32.954 --> 00:16:34.354
and some incense?

00:16:34.387 --> 00:16:36.387
I'll get the shovel.

00:16:36.421 --> 00:16:38.754
Ouri stared for
hours at that cat,

00:16:38.787 --> 00:16:42.487
marveling at how it changed
from a life into an object.

00:16:45.921 --> 00:16:48.221
Ouri...

00:16:53.421 --> 00:16:56.487
Why did you bring him
to a place like this?

00:16:57.721 --> 00:16:59.421
This is where I found him.

00:16:59.454 --> 00:17:02.854
I know he'll start crying
again if he's here.

00:17:05.921 --> 00:17:08.354
I know he will!

00:17:09.554 --> 00:17:10.721
Ouri...

00:17:10.754 --> 00:17:12.387
The best thing
we can do for the dead

00:17:12.421 --> 00:17:13.954
is remember them
for who they were

00:17:13.987 --> 00:17:17.654
and shed tears
for the loss.

00:17:17.687 --> 00:17:20.654
A monk's obligation isn't to
put the dead on a pedestal...

00:17:20.687 --> 00:17:24.487
but to help guide the tears
of those who are left behind.

00:17:24.521 --> 00:17:26.287
So, Ouri...

00:17:26.321 --> 00:17:27.754
It's okay...

00:17:27.787 --> 00:17:30.487
You can cry now.

00:17:37.587 --> 00:17:39.621
I think that was the first
time he ever experienced

00:17:39.654 --> 00:17:42.287
a real emotion.

00:17:43.454 --> 00:17:46.021
In everyday life, people
forget about death...

00:17:46.054 --> 00:17:47.787
And when they're reminded

00:17:47.821 --> 00:17:50.854
because someone close to them
died, they soon forget again...

00:17:50.887 --> 00:17:52.554
But I think it's harder

00:17:52.587 --> 00:17:55.387
for Ouri than it is for
everyone else out there...

00:17:55.421 --> 00:17:57.587
For some reason he thinks
he shouldn't forget.

00:17:57.621 --> 00:17:59.021
But why...?

00:17:59.054 --> 00:18:01.787
It'll just make him suffer
more than he already does...

00:18:01.821 --> 00:18:03.021
There's nothing
to gain there.

00:18:03.054 --> 00:18:04.354
It's time...

00:18:04.387 --> 00:18:06.887
I should be leaving now.

00:18:06.921 --> 00:18:08.687
Where're you going?

00:18:08.721 --> 00:18:12.254
I gotta show my face at the
head temple once in a while.

00:18:21.723 --> 00:18:23.420
Ouri...

00:18:25.183 --> 00:18:26.950
Ouri...

00:18:28.150 --> 00:18:29.717
Ouri...

00:18:29.750 --> 00:18:30.917
Ouri...

00:18:32.117 --> 00:18:32.626
Ouri...

00:18:33.264 --> 00:18:35.964
Have you already
forgotten?

00:18:38.797 --> 00:18:41.730
About little ol' me...?

00:18:41.764 --> 00:18:44.897
But you...
You're dead.

00:18:44.930 --> 00:18:47.064
Ouri, what's
going on in here?

00:18:47.097 --> 00:18:49.397
It's the cat...

00:18:50.797 --> 00:18:52.897
I know you're sad,
but stop crying...

00:18:52.930 --> 00:18:55.130
Go to sleep.

00:18:57.330 --> 00:18:58.964
What's wrong?

00:18:58.997 --> 00:19:01.464
I'm only visible to you...

00:19:01.497 --> 00:19:04.197
Because I am you.

00:19:04.230 --> 00:19:06.930
Have you forgotten
about me...?

00:19:06.964 --> 00:19:09.064
About us...?

00:19:12.064 --> 00:19:13.430
Not again...

00:19:13.464 --> 00:19:16.464
I'm sorry... I think my
mind was kinda wandering.

00:19:16.497 --> 00:19:18.297
Thinking about
that girl again?

00:19:18.330 --> 00:19:19.930
You know--

00:19:22.130 --> 00:19:23.130
Look, you left
her with us,

00:19:23.164 --> 00:19:24.830
but she said
she had to leave.

00:19:24.864 --> 00:19:26.697
I didn't use my best
judgement and I let her go.

00:19:26.730 --> 00:19:27.664
I'm sorry.

00:19:27.697 --> 00:19:30.064
You still don't know
where she is, do you?

00:19:30.097 --> 00:19:33.697
I'll be fine. I gotta
clean this mess up now.

00:19:40.864 --> 00:19:42.397
Excuse me...

00:19:42.430 --> 00:19:44.830
Is your name Makina?

00:19:44.864 --> 00:19:46.464
Depends on who's asking.

00:19:46.497 --> 00:19:50.864
I'm Nozomi Kasuga, you saved
me from that man-eating monster.

00:19:50.897 --> 00:19:54.364
I came by because wanted to say
thank you for saving my life--

00:19:56.130 --> 00:19:58.797
For the good of you and
everything you care about...

00:19:58.830 --> 00:20:01.397
you should forget about
that night and me.

00:20:01.430 --> 00:20:04.064
But Makina, there's
no way I could.

00:20:04.097 --> 00:20:05.164
Go home, kid.

00:20:05.197 --> 00:20:06.830
I don't want to...

00:20:06.864 --> 00:20:08.364
Ouri couldn't possibly
understand you

00:20:08.397 --> 00:20:11.397
or what you are
the way I can.

00:20:11.430 --> 00:20:14.697
He's no good for you and he
doesn't get any of this...

00:20:14.730 --> 00:20:16.964
He doesn't understand
anything about you or death.

00:20:16.997 --> 00:20:18.164
Death?

00:20:18.197 --> 00:20:19.730
Death is forever
and it's something

00:20:19.764 --> 00:20:22.230
only the chosen can
approach without fear...

00:20:22.264 --> 00:20:23.897
Death is beautiful...

00:20:23.930 --> 00:20:26.897
That's why I'm drawn
to you... I get it.

00:20:26.930 --> 00:20:28.830
You get nothing.
Death is death.

00:20:28.864 --> 00:20:30.064
It's as simple as that.

00:20:30.097 --> 00:20:31.264
But...

00:20:31.297 --> 00:20:33.864
You don't know
anything about Ouri.

00:20:33.897 --> 00:20:36.297
You're not familiar
with death at all.

00:20:36.330 --> 00:20:38.364
He is.

00:20:38.397 --> 00:20:40.297
And with you, too?

00:20:51.930 --> 00:20:54.397
Sorry about that.

00:20:54.430 --> 00:20:55.497
I don't know
how it happened,

00:20:55.530 --> 00:20:58.797
but she seems to have gotten
the wrong idea about me.

00:20:58.830 --> 00:21:02.797
So what...? I thought you
were gonna stop coming here.

00:21:04.964 --> 00:21:07.864
I only see him with
you some of the time...

00:21:07.897 --> 00:21:09.697
Do they not allow
cats at your place?

00:21:09.730 --> 00:21:10.997
What?

00:21:11.030 --> 00:21:13.697
Wait, you can see him?

00:21:13.730 --> 00:21:16.397
It's not so dark that I can't
see a cat in front of me...

00:21:16.430 --> 00:21:17.897
And if you're here
to see Keisei,

00:21:17.930 --> 00:21:20.330
he's at the
head temple.

00:21:20.364 --> 00:21:23.264
Do you mind if
I ask you a question?

00:21:23.297 --> 00:21:25.064
Is it about Minai?

00:21:25.097 --> 00:21:28.230
Yeah... Whenever I try
to think about her...

00:21:28.264 --> 00:21:30.930
I realize that I don't
really know that much.

00:21:30.964 --> 00:21:33.064
Would you mind telling me a
couple of things about her?

00:21:33.097 --> 00:21:35.364
What was she like?

00:21:35.397 --> 00:21:37.864
All we can do for the
dead is remember them...

00:21:37.897 --> 00:21:40.964
And cry for the loss
when they're gone.

00:21:40.997 --> 00:21:43.064
Brother told me something
along those lines

00:21:43.097 --> 00:21:44.764
when I was younger...

00:21:44.797 --> 00:21:46.897
But with Minai...

00:21:46.930 --> 00:21:50.230
I don't know enough about
her to remember who she was.

00:21:53.497 --> 00:21:54.964
All I have
to drink is tea.

00:21:54.997 --> 00:21:57.364
Huh?

00:21:57.397 --> 00:21:59.330
Thank you.

00:22:08.964 --> 00:22:13.964
[Music]

00:23:39.364 --> 00:23:42.330
Stars shine in the sky while
people writhe and struggle

00:23:42.364 --> 00:23:43.897
on the ground.

00:23:43.930 --> 00:23:46.164
But in this backwater place
where the living and dead

00:23:46.197 --> 00:23:48.197
have seemed
to switch places,

00:23:48.230 --> 00:23:52.030
even "Stars on the Ground"
can begin to twinkle.

